---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="privacy" description="Privacy policy for personal homelab services">
  <article class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 2026-05-17</em></p>

    <p>
      <strong>neckbozia.com</strong> hosts personal homelab services for the owner
      and a small number of invited users. It is not a commercial product. This
      page documents what data is processed when you sign in via Cloudflare Access.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Email address</strong> — obtained from your identity provider
        (Google, GitHub, or one-time PIN) when you authenticate. Used only to
        verify you are on the allow-list.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Authentication metadata</strong> (IP, timestamp, identity
        provider) — logged by Cloudflare Access for security/audit purposes.
        See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do not collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No analytics, no third-party trackers.</li>
      <li>No sale, sharing, or advertising use of your data.</li>
      <li>No retention beyond what Cloudflare Access keeps for its own audit logs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-party providers</h2>
    <p>
      When you sign in with Google or GitHub, those providers receive a sign-in
      request from this site. Their handling of your data is governed by their
      respective privacy policies:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Reach out at <a href="mailto:neckbozia@gmail.com">neckbozia@gmail.com</a>
      for any privacy questions or to be removed from the allow-list.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
